To enable Developer Mode in Google Chrome, follow these steps:

Open Google Chrome: Launch the Chrome browser on your computer.

Open DevTools:

For Windows and Linux: Press Ctrl + Shift + I or F12.
For macOS: Press Cmd + Option + I.
Access DevTools Settings:

Windows and Linux: Press Ctrl + Shift + P or Cmd + Shift + P on macOS.
Type "settings" and select "Preferences: Open Settings" or navigate to the "Settings" option in the DevTools panel.
Enable Developer Mode:

In the DevTools settings, find the "Experiments" section.
Check the box next to "Enable Developer Tools experiments."
Restart DevTools:

After enabling the Developer Tools experiments, close and reopen the DevTools window by pressing Ctrl + Shift + I or F12.
This will activate Developer Mode in Chrome, giving you access to additional experimental features and settings within the Developer Tools panel.






